# Overview

This ticket involves adding two annotation macros for Scala 2.13 and Scala 3.5+. These annotation macros will add new definitions in the companion object of the trait / class / enum to which they are applied.

The annotation macros are as follows:

 - `@optic`: Adds optics for all terms of the record / enum inside the companion object. Comes in an optional variant, called `@optics_`, which prefixes all optics with an underscore character (`_`) to avoid name collisions. The names of these optics are the same as the term names, except for sum term names, the first letter is lower-cased to avoid colliding with the object of the same name in the same scope.
 - `@schema`: Adds an `implicit` / `given` schema for the record / enum inside the companion object, with the name `<xyz>Schema`, e.g. `personSchema`.

**Note 1**: In the ideal case, applying `@optics` to a sealed trait or enum would result in optics being added to the companion objects of the subtypes of the sealed trait / enum.

## Optics
### Case Class
#### User-Code

```scala
@optics
final case class Person(name: String, age: Int)
```
#### Macro Expansion
```scala
@optics
final case class Person(name: String, age: Int)
object Person {
  val name: Lens[Person, String] = ???
  val age: Lens[Person, Int] = ???
}
```

### Sealed Trait
#### User-Code

```scala
@optics
sealed trait Result[+A]
object Result {
  @optics final case class Success[A](value: A) extends Result[A]
  @optics final case class Failure(error: String) extends Result[Nothing]
  case object Pending extends Result[Nothing]
}
```

#### Macro Expansion

```scala
@optics
sealed trait Result[+A]
object Result {
  @optics final case class Success[A](value: A) extends Result[A]
  object Success {
    val value: Lens[Success[A], A] = ???
  }

  @optics final case class Failure(error: String) extends Result[Nothing]
  object Failure {
    val error: Lens[Failure, String] = ???
  }

  case object Pending extends Result[Nothing]

  val success: Prism[Result[A], Success[A]] = ???
  val failure: Prism[Result[Nothing], Failure] = ???
  val pending: Prism[Result[Nothing], Pending.type] = ???
}
```

### Enum
#### User-Code

```scala
@optics
enum Status {
  case Active(since: Long)
  case Inactive
  case Suspended(reason: String, until: Long)
}
```
#### Macro Expansion
```scala
@optics
enum Status {
  case Active(since: Long)
  case Inactive
  case Suspended(reason: String, until: Long)
}
object Status {
  object Active {
    val since: Lens[Active, Long] = ???
  }
  object Suspended {
    val reason: Lens[Suspended, String] = ???
    val until: Lens[Suspended, Long] = ???
  }

  val active: Prism[Status, Active] = ???
  val inactive: Prism[Status, Inactive.type] = ???
  val suspended: Prism[Status, Suspended] = ???
}
```
